<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Scotland began their Nation's League campaign with a 1-1 draw against Israel on Friday night, ending a 10-month wait for international football. </p>

<p>The hosts opened the scoring at Hampden Park with with Ryan Christie scoring a penalty before Eran Zahavi smacked in a powerful strike after 73 minutes to level. </p>

<p>The result leaves both sides trailing the Czech Republic after the group 2 leaders' 3-1 victory over Slovakia. </p>

<p>More to follow...</p>

<p>Scotland drew 1-1 with Israel on Friday as both sides returned to international football</p>
